{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-95b0b34b586de817","input":{"filename":"roadmap_prioritization_report.md","title":"Roadmap Prioritization Action Report","markdown":"# Roadmap Prioritization Action Report\n\n**Scope** – This report evaluates the three open Roadmap‑Prioritizer records currently in the system and recommends a short‑term execution order.\n\n## Scoring model (assumptions)\n| Factor | Source | Assumed weight |\n|--------|--------|----------------|\n| Impact | `impact` field (numeric) | 1 |\n| Opportunity | `score.opportunity` (1‑10) | 1 |\n| Risk | `score.risk` (1‑10, higher = more risk) | -1 |\n\nPriority = **Impact × Opportunity ÷ Risk**.  Confidence and effort are not recorded, so they are omitted (treated as neutral).  This simple multiplicative model highlights high‑impact items while penalising risk.\n\n## Calculated priorities\n| ID | Title | Impact | Opportunity | Risk | Priority (Impact·Opp÷Risk) |\n|----|-------|--------|-------------|------|----------------------------|\n| **35‑A** | Roadmap prioritizer priority case | 53,095 | 7 | 6 | **≈ 61,980** |\n| **35‑C** | Roadmap prioritizer blocked follow‑up | 25,385 | 2.5 | 8 | **≈ 7,930** |\n| **35‑B** | Roadmap prioritizer routine queue item | 12,955 | 1.3 | 3 | **≈ 5,620** |\n\n## Recommended execution order\n1. **Record 35‑A – “Roadmap prioritizer priority case”** – Highest priority; urgent status, large impact, moderate risk.\n2. **Record 35‑C – “Roadmap prioritizer blocked follow‑up”** – Requires cross‑functional unblock; still a strong opportunity despite higher risk.\n3. **Record 35‑B – “Roadmap prioritizer routine queue item”** – Lower impact and opportunity; suitable for later review.\n\n## Sensitivity notes\n- If the risk of **35‑A** were to increase to 8, its priority drops to ~46,500, still ahead of the others.\n- A 10 % swing in the opportunity rating of **35‑C** (e.g., from 2.5 to 2.75) raises its priority to ~8,735, but does not alter the ranking.\n- Missing confidence/effort data introduces uncertainty; if effort were extreme for **35‑C**, its net value could fall behind **35‑B**.\n\n**Next steps** –\n- Validate effort estimates for each record.\n- Resolve the blocking dependencies for **35‑C**.\n- Re‑run the scoring once confidence scores are available.\n"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:22:00.321Z"}}
